{:synth/id   :s42-vco-voice
 :synth/tags [:vco :pwm :sub :bus-aware :s42-inspired]
 :synth/doc  "VarSaw VCO with LFO-modulated pulse width and sub-oscillator.
  Inspired by multi-voice analog synthesizer VCO architectures
  (see doc/attribution.md); not a licensed reproduction.

  A SinOsc running at :pwm-rate Hz sweeps the VarSaw's width from 0 to 1, creating a
  pulse-width modulation (PWM) effect. :sub-amp (0–1) controls the level of a sub-octave
  pulse at freq/2. Full ADSR envelope. Outputs to :out-bus for use in the :s42 patch."
 :args  {:freq     220
         :amp      0.35
         :attack   0.05
         :decay    0.2
         :sustain  0.7
         :release  1.5
         :pwm-rate 0.8
         :sub-amp  0.4
         :pan      0.0
         :out-bus  8}
 :graph [:out :out-bus
          [:pan2
           [:* [:env-gen [:adsr :attack :decay :sustain :release] :gate :amp]
               [:mix [[:var-saw :freq 0 [:+ 0.5 [:* 0.5 [:sin-osc :pwm-rate]]]]
                      [:* :sub-amp [:pulse [:/ :freq 2] 0.5]]]]]
           :pan]]}
